com: In Ouagadougou, 49.4% of the population aged 15 and older can read and write French. In the capital, French it is the second most spoken language behind Dioula.
In Abidjan, largest city of the country, 57.6% of the inhabitants over 15 can read and write French, and another 11% can speak it but not write it.

French is one of two official languages of Cameroon, the other being English. French is the main language in eight of the ten regions of the country, with English being dominant in the remaining two. [...] The 2005 census found that 57.7% of the population over the age of 12 could speak French, up from 41.1% in 1987.
